from brownli liane brown subject christ my advocate a poem my advocate i sin and straightway posthaste satan fly before the presence of the most high god and make a rail accusation there he say thi soul thi thing of clay and sod ha sin be true that he ha name thy name but i demand hi death for thou hast say soul that sinneth it shall die shall not thy sentence be fulfil is justice dead send now thi wretched sinner to hi doom what other thing can righteou ruler do thu satan do accuse me day and night and every word he speak o god wa true then quickly one rise up from god right hand before whose glory angel veil their eye he speak each jot and tittle of the law must be fulfil the guilty sinner dy but wait suppose hi guilt be all transfer to me and that i pay hi penalty behold my hand my side my foot one day i wa make sin for him and die that he might be present faultles at thy throne and satan fly away full well he know that he could not prevail against such love for every word my dear lord speak wa true by martha snell nicholson i hear thi poem read last night and want to share it with other subscriber of thi newsgroup it such a wonderful bless to see how secure my salvation be because the lord jesu pay for what he do not owe because we have a debt which we be not capable to pay thank and praise be to the savior the lord jesu christ who be seat at the right hand of the majesty on high make intercession for u liane brown internet brownli 